1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,160
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,160 --> 00:00:04,160
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:08,240
My name is Catherine and we're going shopping today at EnglishPod.
我是Catherine，今天我们要在EnglishPod去购物。

4
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:09,240
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:13,260
Today we are going to the store because we want to return a product.
今天我们要去商店，因为想退一件商品。

6
00:00:13,260 --> 00:00:18,240
So maybe the product that we bought had some problem and we want our money back.
可能我们买的商品有问题，想把钱要回来。

7
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:19,240
That's right.
没错。

8
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:22,360
So let's take a listen to today's dialogue and we'll be back in a moment to talk more
那么我们来听一下今天的对话，稍后我们会回来继续讨论

9
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:25,000
about what's going on.
具体发生了什么。

10
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:32,760
Hi, I would like to return this TV.
你好，我想退这台电视。

11
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:34,960
Sure, do you have a receipt?
好的，您有收据吗？

12
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:37,200
Yeah, here you go.
有，给你。

13
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,760
Actually, I also want to return this keyboard.
其实，我还想退这个键盘。

14
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:42,040
Okay.
好的。

15
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:45,800
May I ask what the reason for returning these products is?
请问您退货的原因是什么？

16
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:52,000
The TV flickers a lot when I am watching a movie and at times the image is not very clear.
我看电影时电视闪烁得很厉害，有时画面不太清晰。

17
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,160
I see.
我明白了。

18
00:00:53,160 --> 00:00:54,600
And what about the keyboard?
那键盘呢？

19
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:59,560
I spilled some coffee on it and now it won't work.
我洒了些咖啡在上面，现在它不能用了。

20
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:04,120
I'm sorry ma'am, but we can only exchange or refund defective products.
抱歉女士，我们只能换货或退款给有缺陷的产品。

21
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:07,640
We cannot take responsibility for misuse or damages.
我们不能为误用或损坏负责。

22
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:08,640
Fine.
好吧。

23
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:12,600
I don't know why they make these things so delicate anyways.
反正我也不知道他们为什么把这些东西做得这么脆弱。

24
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:16,360
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

25
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:22,240
So now let's take a look at some of those key words on Language Takeaway.
现在让我们看看“语言要点”中的一些关键词。

26
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:27,400
So we've got a great bunch of words for you here today.
今天我们为大家准备了一组很棒的词汇。

27
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:31,880
The first three are nouns and then afterwards we've got a couple of adjectives to describe
前三个是名词，之后我们有几个形容词来描述

28
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:32,880
those nouns.
这些名词。

29
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:35,040
But first up, we have the word receipt.
但首先，我们有“receipt”这个词。

30
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:36,040
That's right.
没错。

31
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:41,200
So we want to return the television and the worker there asks us if we have the receipt.
我们想退电视，店员问我们有没有收据。

32
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:48,280
Okay, a receipt is a small piece of paper that you receive from a clerk or a server
好的，收据是你从店员或服务员那里收到的一张纸，

33
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:50,160
after you buy something.
在你买东西之后。

34
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:56,160
So if I buy a TV, I will have this small piece of paper that says that I paid $500 for the
所以如果我买了一台电视，我会有一张纸，上面写着我为电视

35
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,160
TV.
付了500美元。

36
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,160
That's right.
没错。

37
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:03,240
So usually they will ask you for the receipt to see when you bought the product and if
所以他们通常会要你的收据，看看你什么时候买的商品，以及

38
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:05,800
you bought the product at that store.
你是否在那家店买的。

39
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:06,800
That's right.
没错。

40
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:12,240
So the receipt has all sorts of information, date, time, method of payment, cost, all those
所以收据上有各种信息：日期、时间、付款方式、价格，所有

41
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,240
things.
这些。

42
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,240
Right.
对。

43
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:17,040
And it's very important if you ever want to return something.
如果你想退货，它非常重要。

44
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:22,600
Now later on in the dialogue, the character explains why he wants to return the TV.
后来在对话中，角色解释了他为什么想退电视。

45
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,040
Now Marco, why does he want to do that?
那么Marco，他为什么想退呢？

46
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:28,680
Well, he has a problem with the TV when he's watching a movie.
嗯，他看电视电影时电视有问题。

47
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:31,200
Basically the image is not very clear.
基本上画面不太清晰。

48
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:33,480
So this is the keyword image.
所以这就是关键词“image”。

49
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,520
So image can mean a couple of different things.
“Image”可以指几种不同的东西。

50
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:40,960
You might hear the word image to mean a photograph or a picture like on a computer.
你可能听到“image”这个词指照片或图片，比如在电脑上。

51
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:47,280
But in this case, the image is how well you can see the images on TV, the things on TV.
但在这里，“image”是指你在电视上看到的画面质量，电视上的东西。

52
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,280
That's right.
没错。

53
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:53,920
So on TV, it's like you're seeing many, many images all at once or very rapidly together.
所以在电视上，就像你同时看到很多很多画面，或者快速连续地看到。

54
00:02:53,920 --> 00:03:00,120
So maybe if you can't see clearly, you say that the image is not clear on the TV.
所以如果你看不清楚，你会说电视上的画面不清晰。

55
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,120
All right.
好的。

56
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:05,520
So if it's fuzzy, like there's gray and black, the image is not clear.
所以如果画面模糊，像有灰色和黑色，那画面就不清晰。

57
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:08,400
You can also say that, you know, I really like my new TV.
你也可以说，你知道，我真的很喜欢我的新电视。

58
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,240
The image is very clear.
画面非常清晰。

59
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,240
That's right.
没错。

60
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,240
Okay.
好的。

61
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:15,560
And not only are we returning a TV, but we're also returning a keyboard.
我们不仅退电视，还退一个键盘。

62
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,680
All right.
好的。

63
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:21,600
A keyboard, a key is something that you can push.
键盘，“key”是你按的东西。

64
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:28,560
But a keyboard is this thing that you use with your computer to type words.
但“keyboard”是你用来在电脑上打字的这个东西。

65
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,560
That's right.
没错。

66
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:34,820
So many of you who are using the website as we speak are using a keyboard and a mouse.
所以很多正在使用网站的朋友，现在就在用键盘和鼠标。

67
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:40,120
So these are probably one of the two most well-known objects when you're using a computer.
所以这些可能是使用电脑时最知名的两个物品之一。

68
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,120
That's right.
没错。

69
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,520
And keyboards come in many different shapes and sizes.
键盘有很多不同的形状和大小。

70
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:47,020
You can buy French keyboards and Russian keyboards.
你可以买法语键盘和俄语键盘。

71
00:03:47,020 --> 00:03:50,480
So keyboard is the general word for this tool.
所以“keyboard”是这种工具的通用词。

72
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,520
Okay.
好的。

73
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:56,840
So we are returning the keyboard and the clerk explains that we can only return it if it
所以我们退键盘，店员解释说我们只能退如果它

74
00:03:56,840 --> 00:04:00,040
is defective, if the product is defective.
有缺陷，如果产品有缺陷。

75
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,040
All right.
好的。

76
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:04,560
So this is one of those adjectives I talked about a minute ago.
所以这是我刚才提到的形容词之一。

77
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,760
Adjectives describe things.
形容词描述事物。

78
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:10,100
So my keyboard is defective or this TV is defective.
所以我的键盘有缺陷，或者这台电视有缺陷。

79
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:12,240
That means it doesn't work.
意思是它不能正常工作。

80
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,240
That's right.
没错。

81
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,760
So we have a defective product.
所以我们有一个有缺陷的产品。

82
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,280
It's not working properly.
它不能正常工作。

83
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:18,420
It has some problem.
它有些问题。

84
00:04:18,420 --> 00:04:24,200
And well, the guy was complaining that he didn't understand why these things like the
嗯，那家伙在抱怨他不明白为什么这些东西，比如

85
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,960
keyboard are so delicate.
键盘，这么脆弱。

86
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,620
All right.
好的。

87
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:33,320
Delicate is something you might see written on the side of a box when you receive a package.
“脆弱”这个词你可能在收到包裹时在盒子侧面看到过。

88
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:36,400
Something that is delicate breaks very easily.
脆弱的东西很容易碎。

89
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,400
That's right.
没错。

90
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,760
So you have to handle with care.
所以你必须小心处理。

91
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:40,960
So for example, glass is very delicate.
比如，玻璃非常脆弱。

92
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:41,960
It can break easily.
它很容易碎。

93
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:42,960
All right.
好的。

94
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:47,600
Glass is delicate but stones, a big rock, that's not delicate.
玻璃是脆弱的，但石头，一块大石头，就不脆弱。

95
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,600
That's right.
没错。

96
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,600
All right.
好的。

97
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,280
So that's all we have for language takeaway.
这就是我们语言要点部分的所有内容。

98
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:55,400
Let's review everything and listen to our dialogue.
让我们回顾一下所有内容，然后听我们的对话。

99
00:04:55,400 --> 00:05:00,200
Hi.
你好。

100
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,400
I would like to return this TV.
我想退掉这台电视。

101
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,400
Sure.
当然。

102
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,400
Do you have a receipt?
你有收据吗？

103
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,400
Yeah.
有。

104
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,400
Here you go.
给你。

105
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:10,240
Actually, I also want to return this keyboard.
实际上，我还想退掉这个键盘。

106
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,240
Okay.
好的。

107
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:15,360
May I ask what the reason for returning these products is?
我能问一下退货的原因吗？

108
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:21,560
The TV flickers a lot when I'm watching a movie and at times the image is not very clear.
我看电影时电视经常闪烁，有时图像不太清晰。

109
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,720
I see.
我明白了。

110
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,200
And what about the keyboard?
那键盘呢？

111
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:29,120
I spilled some coffee on it and now it won't work.
我洒了些咖啡在上面，现在它不工作了。

112
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:33,680
I'm sorry, ma'am, but we can only exchange or refund defective products.
对不起，女士，我们只能换货或退款给有缺陷的产品。

113
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:37,240
We cannot take responsibility for misuse or damages.
我们不能为误用或损坏负责。

114
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,240
Fine.
好吧。

115
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:41,920
I don't know why they make these things so delicate anyways.
反正我不明白他们为什么把这些东西做得这么脆弱。

116
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,920
All right.
好的。

117
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,760
We're back.
我们回来了。

118
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:50,240
So now let's take a look at a couple of phrases we've picked out for to be exact on Fluency
现在让我们看看我们在流利度构建部分挑选的几个短语，

119
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:53,000
Builder.
确切地说。

120
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,880
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建。

121
00:05:54,880 --> 00:06:01,520
The first verb we have today here in Fluency Builder is the main verb in today's dialogue,
今天我们流利度构建中的第一个动词是今天对话中的主要动词，

122
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:02,520
to return.
退货。

123
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:04,920
So I would like to return this TV.
所以我想退掉这台电视。

124
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,920
Okay.
好的。

125
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:11,440
So when you want to give back a product, you don't say I want to give back or anything
所以当你想退回一个产品时，你不会说“我想归还”或类似的话。

126
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,440
like this.
类似这样。

127
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:14,360
You say I want to return this product.
你会说“我想退掉这个产品”。

128
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:16,360
Well, it's not just giving back.
嗯，这不只是归还。

129
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,920
It's giving back and getting your money back.
这是归还并拿回你的钱。

130
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:19,920
That's right.
没错。

131
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:24,720
So to return means that you bring back the product and the store will give you back your
所以“退货”意味着你把产品带回来，商店会把钱退给你。

132
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:25,720
money.
没错。

133
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,720
That's right.
没错。

134
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:31,960
And he wanted to return the TV as we mentioned because the image was not very clear, but
他想退电视，就像我们提到的，因为图像不太清晰，但

135
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:35,600
he also mentioned that the TV flickers a lot.
他还提到电视经常闪烁。

136
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,400
So what is this to flicker?
那么什么是“闪烁”？

137
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:42,640
To flicker is another verb and flicker is something that things with light do.
“闪烁”是另一个动词，闪烁是带光的东西会做的事情。

138
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,040
The light flickers, the TV flickers.
灯光闪烁，电视闪烁。

139
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:48,160
It means the light comes on and off, on and off, on and off.
这意味着灯光一亮一灭，一亮一灭，一亮一灭。

140
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,800
So dark light, dark light.
所以暗亮，暗亮。

141
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,040
It's not very steady.
它不太稳定。

142
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:54,140
It's not like there's a light or dark.
它不是一直亮或一直暗。

143
00:06:54,140 --> 00:06:58,440
And so this is very annoying when you're watching TV because it goes light, dark, light, dark
所以看电视时这很烦人，因为它一亮一暗，一亮一暗，

144
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:00,440
and it's hard to see what's happening.
很难看清发生了什么。

145
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,440
Exactly.
正是。

146
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:05,600
So it's basically just imagine someone is turning on and off the light all the time.
所以基本上就像想象有人一直在开关灯。

147
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,560
That's the same thing that's happening with the TV.
电视上发生的就是同样的事情。

148
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,560
It flickers.
它闪烁。

149
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,560
Exactly.
正是。

150
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:14,520
Or like when a light bulb in your lamp, when a light bulb is dying, it flickers.
或者像你台灯里的灯泡，当灯泡快坏时，它会闪烁。

151
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,520
That's right.
没错。

152
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,520
All right.
好的。

153
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:23,200
So we wanted to actually return these goods and the clerk explained that we can exchange
所以我们实际上想退掉这些商品，店员解释说我们可以换货

154
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:26,080
or we can refund defective products.
或者退款给有缺陷的产品。

155
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,080
Okay.
好的。

156
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,520
These are two important verbs.
这是两个重要的动词。

157
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:32,760
Exchange means to trade one thing for another.
“换货”意味着用一件东西交换另一件。

158
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:36,960
So when I go to a foreign country, I exchange money, right?
所以当我去外国时，我换钱，对吧？

159
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:41,280
I can exchange Japanese yen for American dollars.
我可以把日元换成美元。

160
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:48,560
But at a store like an electronic store, I can exchange my TV that I don't like for maybe
但在像电子商店这样的店里，我可以把我讨厌的电视换成也许

161
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:52,620
a really good MP3 player or something like that.
一个很好的MP3播放器之类的东西。

162
00:07:52,620 --> 00:07:58,680
So that's what happens usually if maybe your TV is broken or it had some problem, you exchange
所以通常如果你的电视坏了或出了什么问题，你会去换货。

163
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:02,040
it for a new one, right?
换一个新的，对吧？

164
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:04,100
But maybe you don't want the TV anymore.
但也许你不再想要那台电视了。

165
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,240
Maybe you changed your mind.
也许你改变了主意。

166
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:07,360
So you want to get a refund.
所以你想退款。

167
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:11,000
So refund, you hear this word fund, it has to do with money.
所以退款，你听到这个词里有“fund”，它和钱有关。

168
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,720
A refund means that the store will give you all your money back.
退款意味着商店会把你的钱全部退还。

169
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:20,620
So if I refund my TV, I give my TV to the store, the store gives me $500 or whatever
所以如果我退掉我的电视，我把电视还给商店，商店给我500美元或电视原来的价钱。

170
00:08:20,620 --> 00:08:24,680
the money for the TV was, and I can buy anything else anywhere else.
然后我可以在任何地方买任何东西。

171
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,680
That's right.
没错。

172
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:30,680
So this is what happens when you get a refund, very different from exchanging the goods.
所以这就是退款的情况，和换货很不一样。

173
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:37,360
And finally, the clerk explained that they cannot take responsibility for misuse or damages.
最后，店员解释说他们不能对误用或损坏负责。

174
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:39,040
So remember this as a phrase.
所以记住这个短语。

175
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:42,300
This is really important to take responsibility.
这真的很重要：承担责任。

176
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:47,200
It means that if something goes wrong, you will take responsibility for it.
意思是如果出了问题，你会为此负责。

177
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,760
You will handle it.
你会处理它。

178
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:49,760
All right.
好的。

179
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:55,680
So for example, the store says that it can't take responsibility if something is broken.
比如，商店说如果东西坏了，他们不能承担责任。

180
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,360
That means that they won't pay you back money.
这意味着他们不会退钱给你。

181
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,360
That's right.
没错。

182
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:03,360
So if you buy a TV and you accidentally get it wet or you get water inside and this is
所以如果你买了一台电视，不小心把它弄湿了，或者水进去了，导致它损坏。

183
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:09,440
why it gets damaged, then the store cannot take responsibility for this damage.
那么商店不能为这个损坏承担责任。

184
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,520
Or you could say the other way around.
或者你也可以反过来用。

185
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:15,560
You could say, if you're at the office and you make a mistake on a report, you say, listen,
你可以说，如果你在办公室，在报告上犯了个错误，你说：“听着，老板，我真的很抱歉。”

186
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:16,640
boss, I'm really sorry.
我真的很抱歉。

187
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:20,100
I take full responsibility for this mistake.
我对这个错误负全责。

188
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:23,880
You can punish me or you can make me do it again.
你可以惩罚我，或者让我重做。

189
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:26,960
But I take responsibility means that I say it's my fault.
但“我承担责任”意味着我说这是我的错。

190
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:27,960
Right.
对。

191
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,960
You're guilty.
你有罪。

192
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:29,960
All right.
好的。

193
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:30,960
So that's all we have for Fluency Builder.
这就是我们“流利度构建”的全部内容。

194
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:36,800
Let's listen to our dialogue one last time and we can review everything we've just learned.
让我们最后听一遍对话，回顾我们刚学的一切。

195
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:44,040
Hi, I would like to return this TV.
你好，我想退掉这台电视。

196
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,160
Sure.
好的。

197
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,160
Do you have a receipt?
你有收据吗？

198
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,160
Yeah.
有。

199
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,160
Here you go.
给你。

200
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:51,960
Actually, I also want to return this keyboard.
实际上，我还想退掉这个键盘。

201
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:52,960
OK.
好的。

202
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:57,080
May I ask what the reason for returning these products is?
我能问一下退货的原因吗？

203
00:09:57,080 --> 00:10:03,280
The TV flickers a lot when I am watching a movie and at times the image is not very clear.
我看电影时电视经常闪烁，有时画面不太清晰。

204
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:04,440
I see.
我明白了。

205
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,920
And what about the keyboard?
那键盘呢？

206
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:10,800
I spilled some coffee on it and now it won't work.
我洒了些咖啡在上面，现在它不工作了。

207
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:15,400
I'm sorry, ma'am, but we can only exchange or refund defective products.
对不起，女士，我们只能换货或退款有缺陷的产品。

208
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:18,960
We cannot take responsibility for misuse or damages.
我们不能对误用或损坏负责。

209
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,960
Fine.
好吧。

210
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:27,360
I don't know why they make these things so delicate anyways.
反正我也不知道他们为什么把这些东西做得这么脆弱。

211
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:32,280
So returning goods is a very useful thing if you maybe bought a TV at a department store
所以退货是一件很有用的事，如果你可能在百货商店或电子商店买了电视。

212
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:37,080
or an electronic store, then you would want to return it if you had some problems.
那么如果出了问题，你会想退货。

213
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:39,800
Now, how easy or difficult is it to do?
现在，做这件事有多容易或多难？

214
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:43,440
Because in theory, in the dialogue, it seems like it's really easy.
因为理论上，在对话中，看起来很容易。

215
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,600
It depends on the store, of course.
当然，这取决于商店。

216
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,680
Some stores make it easier to do this.
有些商店让退货更容易。

217
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:49,680
Some stores make it harder.
有些商店让退货更难。

218
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:54,400
I can tell you in most stores, if you don't have a receipt, it's probably very difficult.
我可以告诉你，在大多数商店，如果你没有收据，可能非常困难。

219
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,400
Really?
真的吗？

220
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:56,400
Yes.
是的。

221
00:10:56,400 --> 00:11:00,120
But a lot of stores have something else that they sell you or give you when you buy something.
但很多商店在你买东西时还会卖给你或给你别的东西。

222
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,720
It's called a warranty.
它叫保修。

223
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:06,160
And this is something that will help protect you if you take the TV home and you have a
这能保护你，如果你把电视带回家后出了问题。

224
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,160
problem.
出了问题。

225
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,160
Right.
对。

226
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:11,440
That means that they will come fix it or they will give you a new one without any questions
这意味着他们会来修好它，或者给你一个新的，不问任何问题。

227
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:12,720
about what happened.
不问发生了什么。

228
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:18,880
Now, not only can you return goods such as TVs, electronics or maybe clothes, but in
现在，你不仅可以退货像电视、电子产品或衣服这样的东西。

229
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:23,560
some cases also things that you buy at the supermarket, like maybe chicken.
在某些情况下，还有你在超市买的东西，比如鸡肉。

230
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:27,480
I've heard that maybe sometimes you buy chicken and you open it up that same day and it's
我听说过，有时你买鸡肉，当天打开它就坏了。

231
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,480
gone bad.
坏了。

232
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,480
Really?
真的吗？

233
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:32,480
I've never had that experience, but I think it makes sense.
我从未有过这种经历，但我觉得这说得通。

234
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:33,760
It depends where you buy it, of course.
当然，这取决于你在哪里买。

235
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:34,760
Right.
对。

236
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:38,640
Obviously at a supermarket and you show the receipt or maybe milk.
显然在超市，你出示收据，或者牛奶。

237
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,760
Maybe that's gone bad sometimes or yogurt.
也许有时牛奶或酸奶坏了。

238
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,840
Well, because they probably shouldn't sell it if it's bad.
嗯，因为它们可能不应该卖坏的东西。

239
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:44,840
Exactly.
完全正确。

240
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:47,760
If you tell them that they sold you bad milk, they'll give you a new one.
如果你告诉他们他们卖给你坏牛奶，他们会给你一个新的。

241
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:48,760
Exactly.
没错。

242
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,080
So that's called an exchange.
这就叫换货。

243
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:52,720
You would exchange the bad one for the good one.
你会把坏的那个换成好的那个。

244
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:53,720
Right.
对。

245
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,720
You wouldn't get your money back.
你不会拿回你的钱。

246
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:55,720
No.
不会。

247
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:56,720
Maybe, maybe not.
也许，也许不会。

248
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,720
Maybe.
也许吧。

249
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,720
All right.
好了。

250
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,040
So that's all the time we have for today, but this is actually a very interesting topic
今天的时间就到这里，但这其实是个很有趣的话题，

251
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:02,960
because it has to do a lot with customer service.
因为它跟客户服务有很大关系。

252
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:07,360
So let us know what your experience is with customer service, with returning something.
所以，告诉我们你在客户服务、退货方面的经历吧。

253
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,480
Is it very easy?
很容易吗？

254
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,800
Very difficult?
很难吗？

255
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,760
Actually some stores don't even accept returns.
实际上有些商店甚至不接受退货。

256
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:14,720
They say once you buy it, you cannot return it.
他们说一旦你买了，就不能退。

257
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,000
All sales final.
所有销售都是最终决定。

258
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,400
Yeah, exactly.
是啊，没错。

259
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,600
So let us know.
所以告诉我们吧。

260
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,920
Are refunds or exchanges common where you come from?
在你那里，退款或换货常见吗？

261
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:25,360
And have you ever had a bad experience where you bought something and it didn't work when
你有没有过糟糕的经历，买了东西回家后

262
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,360
you got home?
发现它不能用？

263
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,360
Let us know.
告诉我们吧。

264
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:28,360
Our website is EnglishPod.com.
我们的网站是 EnglishPod.com。

265
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,360
All right.
好了。

266
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,360
We'll see you guys there.
我们会在那里见你们。

267
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:48,640
Thanks again.
再次感谢。
